title: Euromillions' youngest Brit winner 'SUING Lotto for ruining her life'
text:
NO-ONE UNDERSTANDS: Jane Park complains about life as a millionaire “At times it feels like winning the lottery has ruined my life” Jane Park 
Jane was only 17 when she bagged the £1 million prize with her first-ever ticket. 
But despite going from living on a council estate to owning two properties, Jane claims winning the money has ruined her life. 
The former admin temp is placing the blame firmly at the door of Camelot, who she claims should not have let her buy a ticket at such a young age. 
FACEBOOK REVEALED: Jane tells all about her life 
Jane, now 21, is even considering legal action against the lottery organisers for negligence. 
She told The People: "At times it feels like winning the lottery has ruined my life. 
"I thought it would make my life ten times better but it's made it ten times worse. Boob job Britain Sunday, 26th June 2016 Girls are back in love with bigger boobs and we’ve got the pictures to prove it. Check out what everyone is getting THIS summer. 1 / 9 
"I wish I had no money most days. I say to myself, 'my life would be so much easier if I hadn't won'." 
Jane, who has named herself "Jane Sexual Park" on Twitter where she films herself necking MD 20/20, has not avoided the headlines since her big win. 
The busty blonde has flashed her surgically enhanced chest several times in front of cameras , and is facing drink-driving charges at an Edinburgh McDonald's, which she denies. @deanoshades eating grapes n drinking your dug pic.twitter.com/PVbhTN4aBx — jane sexual park (@janeparkx) January 29, 2017 
And Jane has claimed that her winnings have caused her more stress than people would believe. 
She added: "People look at me and think, 'I wish I had her lifestyle, I wish I had her money'. But they don't realise the extent of my stress. 
"I have material things but apart from that my life is empty. What is my purpose in life?" 
A Camelot spokesman told The People they have offered Jane ongoing support and will continue to do so. Related articles
